The safety guidelines are designed to guarantee that the server does not add congestion to a congested network. The following mechanisms should help in fulfilling this objective:
	The server SHOULD compare the measured transport parameters of the 0-RTT connection with those of the 1-RTT connection;
	The server MUST NOT send more than a recommended maximum initial window in the first transmission of data. This value could be based on .
